File: A health professional takes a nasal swab to test for the COVID-19 coronavirus. AFP/Phill Magakoe JOHANNESBURG - A total of 15,036 new COVID-19 infections have been reported in the last 24-hours. Gauteng accounts for just over 9,800 of them. READ: COVID-19 in SA: Stricter restrictions recommended The NICD said 122 COVID-19 related deaths have also been recorded. A total of 55,920 tests were conducted in the last 24 hours.